 I made my monk because:<br>
<br>
I wanted to be able to explore (FD+Sneak), but still solo as well (Good damage) and contribute at the high level.<br>
<br>
My original character was a paladin, through various breaks and starts on alternates (including a monk) he made it to 46~ pre kunark. My main problem with him was that even with basically the 'best' weapon available to him (Mithril Two Hander, so uber!) his damage output was rather pathetic. Also, at the raid level (did lots of dragon runs and at least once to each plane pre kunark) he basically was a weak damage dealer who occasionally got to toss an ineffectual heal out to an enchanter.<br>
<br>
So shortly after Kunark came out, I pretty much retired him, moved to the newest server, and started a rogue. That rogue made it to level 20, and for various reasons never made it beyond that. =p<br>
<br>
Moved back to my original server after a month or two break, started another rogue, and he made it to a little over 40 before I discovered what I didn't like about rogues. They did great damage, and that was it. Sneak/hide was cool for exploring, but once something saw you, you were toast. I was also sick of grouping with warriors using a Wurmslayer who were completely unable to taunt off me, so my great damage was for naught.<br>
<br>
So I quit for a year and a half, came back and started Kwaid in honor of an old guildmate and good friend, and he is now as high level as I've ever been (56 and moving towards 57 fast). There are times where grouped I say to myself, 'If I was playing a rogue here we'd be doing better', but honestly its not that often, and the higher I get the less I seem to think it. I couldn't play last night, but I would imagine for what my playstyle is I will see little if any change. I haven't seriously solo'd for xp in 6~ levels, in a group of any size I'm there to do damage and possibly pull (have a 60 monk guildmate who usually pulls). That doesn't mean I like the nerf, especially since all reports seem to indicate that the NToV/VT equipped monks aren't seeing much if any change, where as the mediocre equipped monks are getting slaughtered. =/  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showPrevMessage?topicID=386.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showNextMessage?topicID=386.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=386.topic&index=0><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.emailToFriend?topicID=386.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm17.threadControl?topicID=386.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness4